JOHANNESBURG - A section of the building housing the offices of Gauteng Premier David Makhura was in flames, officials reported on Friday morning. The City of Johannesburg Fire Department will investigate the cause of the fire and the damage thereof, Makhura s spokesperson Phumla Sekhonyane said.READ: Gauteng premier's building on fireAll staff had been safely evacuated and Johannesburg emergency services were on site.The cause of the fire was unknown.Photographs showed flames and smoke billowing from the top of the building. Additional reporting by African News Agency eNCA